  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Cook the diced bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until crispy. Remove from heat and set aside.",
    "Add the olive oil to the same skillet and cook the sliced onion until softened. Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the sliced potatoes to the skillet and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Transfer the potato mixture to a 9x13-inch baking dish and stir in the cooked bacon, milk, butter, salt, and pepper.",
    "Top the potato mixture with the grated cheddar cheese and chopped parsley.",
    "Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the potatoes are tender.",
    "Sprinkle with grated nutmeg to taste and serve hot."
  ],
